	<logo>https://static.globalissues.org/i/globalissues/logo-feed.jpg</logo><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318</id><title>Gaza: UN urges Israel to allow fuel into Strip</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The crisis in Gaza is worsening, UN humanitarians warned on Monday, as ongoing hostilities and access restrictions drive displaced communities deeper into despair.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: UN urges Israel to allow fuel into Strip”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40317</id><title>Gaza: ‘Unbearable’ suffering continues, UN official tells Security Council</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40317" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/15-05-2025-UN_Photo-SecCo_2.jpeg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/15-05-2025-UN_Photo-SecCo_2.jpeg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The humanitarian crisis in Gaza is deepening at an alarming rate, a senior United Nations official warned on Monday, as Israeli military operations and attacks on civilians seeking aid continue to exact a devastating toll on lives and infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40317&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: ‘Unbearable’ suffering continues, UN official tells Security Council”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/15-05-2025-UN_Photo-SecCo_2.jpeg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40316</id><title>Report reveals significant rise in civilian casualties and rights violations in Ukraine</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40316" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/10-04-2025_UNOCHA_Ukraine-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/10-04-2025_UNOCHA_Ukraine-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Civilian casualties and violations in Ukraine have significantly escalated in recent months, including a sharp rise in often deadly drone attacks, the UN human rights office, OHCHR, said in a report published on Monday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40316&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Report reveals significant rise in civilian casualties and rights violations in Ukraine”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/10-04-2025_UNOCHA_Ukraine-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40315</id><title>Afghanistan: Surging returns from Iran overwhelm fragile support systems, UN agencies warn</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40315" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UNNCR-Afghanistan-03.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UNNCR-Afghanistan-03.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;More than 700,000 Afghan migrants have returned from Iran so far this year, including 256,000 in June alone, the UN International Organization for Migration (IOM) reported on Monday, warning of immense pressures on Afghanistan’s overstretched support systems.   &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40315&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Afghanistan: Surging returns from Iran overwhelm fragile support systems, UN agencies warn”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UNNCR-Afghanistan-03.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40314</id><title>Human rights can be a ‘strong lever for progress’ in climate change, says UN rights chief</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40314" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-01-2025_IFRC_Russia.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-01-2025_IFRC_Russia.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The UN’s top rights official on Monday urged the international community to confront the growing human rights implications of climate change.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40314&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Human rights can be a ‘strong lever for progress’ in climate change, says UN rights chief”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-01-2025_IFRC_Russia.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40313</id><title>Every hour, 100 people die of loneliness-related causes, UN health agency reports</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40313" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/10-10-2022-UNICEF-UN0214238-Timor-Leste.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/10-10-2022-UNICEF-UN0214238-Timor-Leste.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One in six people are affected by loneliness, with significant implications for health and well-being, according to a new report from the UN World Health Organization (WHO). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40313&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Every hour, 100 people die of loneliness-related causes, UN health agency reports”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/10-10-2022-UNICEF-UN0214238-Timor-Leste.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40312</id><title>After the big development pledges in Seville, UN says action starts now</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40312" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UN-Photo-FFD4-opening-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UN-Photo-FFD4-opening-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now the big promises have been formally adopted in the Spanish city of Seville to turbocharge financing for sustainable development, how are the ambitious goals going to be met – and how quickly?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40312&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “After the big development pledges in Seville, UN says action starts now”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/30-06-2025-UN-Photo-FFD4-opening-02.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40311</id><title>It’s time to finance our future and ‘change course’, Guterres tells world leaders in Sevilla</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40311" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/28-6-2025-sevilla-GV-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/28-6-2025-sevilla-GV-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;“We’re here in Sevilla to change course,” the UN chief told world leaders on Monday, calling on them to grasp a once-in-a-decade opportunity to close a $4 trillion financing gap facing developing countries to meet sustainable development goals – and build a better world for all.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40311&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “It’s time to finance our future and ‘change course’, Guterres tells world leaders in Sevilla”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/28-6-2025-sevilla-GV-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40310</id><title>Funding shortages threaten relief for millions of Sudanese refugees: WFP</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40310" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/24-06-2025-UNHCR-Sudan.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/24-06-2025-UNHCR-Sudan.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Critical shortfalls in global humanitarian funding now threaten millions of Sudanese refugees fleeing war to seek refuge in neighbouring countries, the UN World Food Programme (WFP) said on Monday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40310&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Funding shortages threaten relief for millions of Sudanese refugees: WFP”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/24-06-2025-UNHCR-Sudan.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40309</id><title>LIVE: World leaders in Sevilla launch ambitious push to finance the future</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40309" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/29-06-2025-FFD4-sevilla-03.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/29-06-2025-FFD4-sevilla-03.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From rising debt and shrinking investment, to the aid funding crisis and struggles to meet ambitious development goals, the global financial system is failing the people it&#039;s supposed to serve: fixing that is the challenge facing world leaders gathered in Spain&#039;s sweltering southern jewel of Sevilla this week, as the UN&#039;s 4th International Conference on Financing for Development gets underway. Follow our live Meetings Coverage below; app users can catch all the action from the opening session here and you&#039;ll find all related stories on our special dedicated page right here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40309&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “LIVE: World leaders in Sevilla launch ambitious push to finance the future”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/29-06-2025-FFD4-sevilla-03.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry></feed><!-- 0.0011s -->